OL,3,CThe defiant pit community that united
OL,4,Cafter being 'destroyed'
OL,6,FAt its height, Grimethorpe's colliery
OL,7,Fhad been the most productive in
OL,8,FEurope, bringing a million tons of
OL,9,Fcoal to the surface each year.
OL,11,FThe pit and its related industries
OL,12,Femployed 6,000 workers.
OL,14,FWhen the Conservative government
OL,15,Fannounced a raft of closures and
OL,16,Fminers went on strike, the community,
OL,17,Fand many others like it, was plunged
OL,18,Finto poverty and despair.
