OL,3,CThe defiant pit community that united
OL,4,Cafter being 'destroyed'
OL,6,F"So Maggie Thatcher, did she do us a
OL,7,Ffavour, or did she not do us a favour?
OL,8,FIt's swings and roundabouts. I've sort
OL,9,Fof matured now and mellowed.
OL,11,F"Life goes on, you can't bear a grudge
OL,12,Fforever and a ruddy day."
OL,14,FCllr Houghton said:" I think this
OL,15,Fcommunity can be really proud that not
OL,16,Fonly did it deal with the strike, did
OL,17,Fit deal with the pit closures, but
OL,18,Fit's given itself a future as well."
